column5: Bright Angel Trail to Plateau Point
First run in the new shoes - Nike Air Zoom Structure 24s
Overcast clouds, 14C, Feels like 14C, Humidity 81%, Wind 3km/h from NNW - by Klimat.app

Running research session 1, 30C & 70% Humidity. 
5 min warm up, 3.5km @ 4.16, 2km on self propelled treadmill
Pretty happy with sub 3 and Sophies PB
column11:
82kg pre race
Morning Routine: 130mins pre race - 2 bananas w/peanut butter & LCM bar. 
120mins pre race - toilet, shower, toilet. 
90mins pre race - 1km walk, 1km jog. 
60mins pre race - toilet 
30mins pre race - 1 x gel
20mins pre race - pee

Race Nutrition: 1 x gel pre race, 7km, 14km, 25km (w/caffeine), 30km (w/caffeine). 4 snakes. Water and Gatorade at most drink stations. I wish I had 2 more gels and some salt. 

Notes: Stomach felt fantastic all race, quads and left calf got tight at about 22km. 30km they were really tight. I was really worried I was going to cramp for the last 2km, but nothing to worry about in the end. Fantastic conditions, race went to plan. Shouldve started way closer to the front, but being with a pacer for the last 15km when the traffic was bad was fantastic.
